No. She did, but don't involve her, OK?

01:18:38.298 --> 01:18:42.792
- Why not?
- She's not exactly proud of what she did.

01:18:42.928 --> 01:18:46.623
OK. No problem, Jack.
But could I at least talk to her?

01:18:46.723 --> 01:18:51.211
- Well, that's up to her. I...
- OK. Look, I'll take care of that.

01:18:51.311 --> 01:18:53.839
Jack, could you hold on just one second?

01:18:56.650 --> 01:19:00.220
- Jack, when can I see this stuff?
- Uh, any time.

01:19:00.320 --> 01:19:03.932
Great. Can I give you a call
this afternoon? Where can I reach you?

01:19:04.032 --> 01:19:08.312
- I'll be home all day.
- OK. I'll call you then. So long.

01:19:08.412 --> 01:19:10.814
- Oh, hi.
- I just spoke to Donahue.

01:19:10.914 --> 01:19:14.318
- Who's he?
- A TV newsman. Does investigative news.

01:19:14.418 --> 01:19:16.713
Oh, I don't watch the news.

01:19:16.753 --> 01:19:18.753
What?

01:19:18.755 --> 01:19:21.575
- What's he wanna do?
- He said he'd put it on the air.

01:19:21.675 --> 01:19:24.161
- He'd call later and set up a meeting.
- Great.

01:19:24.261 --> 01:19:28.040
He also said he'd like me to go on TV
and say that it's what I saw and heard.

01:19:28.140 --> 01:19:30.542
Said the tape wouldn't be
any good without it.

01:19:30.642 --> 01:19:35.589
- But he'd also like you to go on too.
- Oh, no. I don't want any part of it.

01:19:35.689 --> 01:19:39.092
Well, I know you don't,
but would you at least speak to him?

01:19:39.192 --> 01:19:41.434
No, I don't want to.

01:19:41.570 --> 01:19:44.598
Come on, Sally. They can't say
we're both hearing things.

01:19:44.698 --> 01:19:48.352
If we get this out in the open,
there's no one that can hurt us.

01:19:48.452 --> 01:19:50.813
All right, I'll think about it, OK?

01:19:50.913 --> 01:19:56.026
At City Hall this morning, Chief Inspector
Mackey held a news conference.

01:19:56.126 --> 01:19:59.655
He said a preliminary investigation
into Governor McRyan's death...

01:19:59.755 --> 01:20:02.491
...revealed that he was the victim
of a freak accident.

01:20:02.591 --> 01:20:04.117
- Bullshit.
- Also in the news...

01:20:04.217 --> 01:20:06.537
...is the bizarre sex killing of Mary Robert,

01:20:06.637 --> 01:20:10.123
a 22-year-old receptionist
from the Center City area.

01:20:10.223 --> 01:20:14.169
Her body was found at 10 a.m.
in the Reading Terminal excavation site...

01:20:14.269 --> 01:20:18.944
...after police received a tip
from an anonymous caller.

01:20:30.869 --> 01:20:32.521
The girl had been strangled,

01:20:32.621 --> 01:20:36.859
then repeatedly stabbed with a pointed
instrument across her stomach and groin.

01:20:36.959 --> 01:20:40.112
The stab marks were
in the pattern of a Liberty Bell.

01:20:40.212 --> 01:20:43.949
The police are at a loss
to explain this grotesque mutilation.

01:20:44.049 --> 01:20:46.493
We asked forensic psychologist
Dr Joseph Fuchs...

01:20:46.593 --> 01:20:50.164
...what connection there might be
between the bell-shaped wounds...

01:20:50.264 --> 01:20:52.583
...and the upcoming
Liberty Day celebration.

01:20:52.683 --> 01:20:55.627
- Hi. This is Sally.
- Hi, Sally. Frank Donahue here.

01:20:55.727 --> 01:20:58.130
Yeah, you were supposed to call Jack.

01:20:58.230 --> 01:21:02.467
It's the damnedest thing. I can't get Jack
on the phone to arrange a meeting.

01:21:02.567 --> 01:21:07.931
His line's been busy
all day. So I thought I'd give you a ring.

01:21:08.031 --> 01:21:10.031
Yeah? So?

01:21:27.509 --> 01:21:31.163
Something's wrong with your phone.
I kept gettin' a busy signal.

01:21:31.263 --> 01:21:34.249
What do you mean?
I've been waitin' for Donahue's call.

01:21:34.349 --> 01:21:38.128
- He was gettin' a busy signal too.
- How do you know that?

01:21:38.228 --> 01:21:41.298
He called me. We're meeting
at 30th Street Station at five.

01:21:41.398 --> 01:21:42.841
How did he get your number?

01:21:42.941 --> 01:21:44.927
- Didn't you give it to him?
- No.

01:21:45.027 --> 01:21:47.805
Well, reporters have a way
of gettin' numbers.

01:21:47.905 --> 01:21:53.685
- So I'll give him the tape and the film.
- Why didn't he call me back?

01:21:53.827 --> 01:21:56.772
He wants to meet me alone,
to talk me into goin' on the air.

01:21:56.872 --> 01:21:58.982
No, he should've called me back.

01:21:59.082 --> 01:22:01.985
- Your phone is out of order.
- It is not out of order.

01:22:02.085 --> 01:22:04.780
I've been here all day.
I made a phone call.

01:22:04.880 --> 01:22:07.430
Here. Listen.

01:22:07.716 --> 01:22:11.161
- Maybe the phone company's in on it.
- No, something's not right.

01:22:11.261 --> 01:22:15.541
Let's just meet him. I'll give him the tape
and the film and get it over with.

01:22:15.641 --> 01:22:18.531
Once he's got the film, that's it.

01:22:20.020 --> 01:22:23.006
All right. He wants to meet you, right?

01:22:23.106 --> 01:22:25.592
- Yeah.
- OK. You're gonna go and meet him.

01:22:25.692 --> 01:22:28.387
If he sounds OK,
you'll give him the film and tape.

01:22:28.487 --> 01:22:30.889
- Where are you gonna be?
- Close.

01:22:30.989 --> 01:22:34.049
- I don't get it.
- I'm gonna wire you.

01:22:34.201 --> 01:22:36.019
Wire me? What for?

01:22:36.119 --> 01:22:41.474
I'm gonna cover all the bases.
Nobody's gonna fuck me this time.

01:22:42.292 --> 01:22:46.488
This way, if he disappears with the film,
he can't deny it cos I got him on tape.

01:22:46.588 --> 01:22:49.449
Aren't you gettin' a little paranoid here?

01:22:49.549 --> 01:22:53.453
He's a newsman. This is a very big story.
Why isn't he gonna put it on the air?

01:22:53.553 --> 01:22:57.875
Look what happened when I took it
to the police. They erased it, right?

01:22:57.975 --> 01:23:01.170
- What are you doin'?
- Making a copy, to cover ourselves.

01:23:01.270 --> 01:23:04.095
Yeah? Well, what about the film?

01:23:04.231 --> 01:23:07.342
I can't make a copy now.
I don't have time to do that.

01:23:07.442 --> 01:23:10.262
- OK, OK. Bring on the wire.
- Take off your coat.

01:23:10.362 --> 01:23:12.657
OK. Let's get it over with.

01:23:27.045 --> 01:23:31.325
- So you travel a lot, huh?
- Oh, yeah. I been all over the place.

01:23:31.425 --> 01:23:33.410
Yeah, I travelled once.

01:23:33.510 --> 01:23:38.290
So, uh... you say you got
about 60 minutes and about 60 dollars?

01:23:38.390 --> 01:23:40.959
- Oh, no. Did I say that?
- Yeah, you did say that.

01:23:41.059 --> 01:23:45.797
No, I think... about 20 minutes
and about 20 dollars is what I've got.

01:23:45.897 --> 01:23:49.760
Gee, it's too bad you don't have
about 40 minutes and about 40 dollars.

01:23:49.860 --> 01:23:53.096
- Yeah, that's too bad.
- Yeah, that's too bad.

01:23:53.196 --> 01:23:56.683
What I've got is about 20 minutes
and about 20 dollars.

01:23:56.783 --> 01:24:00.062
The trains are never on time.

01:24:00.162 --> 01:24:02.439
They're notorious. Know what I mean?

01:24:02.539 --> 01:24:05.442
I bet you at least got 30 minutes. At least.

01:24:05.542 --> 01:24:09.071
- Do I have to have 30 minutes?
- At least 30 minutes.

01:24:09.171 --> 01:24:14.743
You know, I believe I do have
about 30 minutes and about 30 dollars.

01:24:14.843 --> 01:24:17.579
Great. I'll make a quick phone call...

01:24:17.679 --> 01:24:20.791
...and meet you in the back
of the waiting room in two minutes.

01:24:20.891 --> 01:24:25.379
That should be two dollars off but... we'll
let you go this time. Know what I mean?

01:24:25.479 --> 01:24:28.549
No, I don't know what you mean.
You know what I mean?

01:24:28.649 --> 01:24:31.709
- See ya.
- Yeah. I know what you mean.

01:24:35.530 --> 01:24:37.564
Hey, Ralphie.

01:24:40.619 --> 01:24:42.914
I gotta have a 20.

01:24:48.627 --> 01:24:53.121
Just enjoy your puppet show.
Have a good Liberty Day.

01:25:49.104 --> 01:25:53.383
- Slower. Aw, shit.
- Some hotshot sailor you are.

01:25:53.483 --> 01:25:57.721
That's ridiculous. Why don't you grow up
and learn a thing or two, sailor boy?

01:25:57.821 --> 01:26:01.476
I've been on a sh...
Ten for you, baby. Ten.

01:26:01.783 --> 01:26:07.648
- Hey, what about my $30? You fuck.
- You blew it. You know what I mean?

01:26:08.290 --> 01:26:10.323
Shit.

01:28:44.279 --> 01:28:48.308
...Attention, please.
This will be the last call...

01:28:48.408 --> 01:28:53.559
...for the Broadway Limited
to Pittsburgh and Chicago.

01:28:54.623 --> 01:28:59.451
All passengers travelling
all the way to Chicago,

01:28:59.586 --> 01:29:03.997
and passengers holding space
in car 4140...

01:29:22.734 --> 01:29:26.763
- Aren't you overdoin' this a little bit?
- We've got nothin' to lose.

01:29:26.863 --> 01:29:31.101
If I had any sense, I'd take this stuff
and dump it in the trash, and that'd be it.

01:29:31.201 --> 01:29:35.063
- Yeah, but I got the original at home, so...
- So why all this?

01:29:35.163 --> 01:29:38.692
Because of Manny's film. I told you.
We gotta be careful with it.

01:29:38.792 --> 01:29:45.082
You know, the only real trouble
I ever got into was when I was too careful.

01:29:47.175 --> 01:29:49.286
Give me a sound level. Count to 10, slow.

01:29:49.386 --> 01:29:51.538
- One, two, three, four...
- No, just normal.

01:29:51.638 --> 01:29:54.750
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

01:29:54.850 --> 01:29:57.836
- All right.
- Come on. We gotta get goin' here.

01:29:57.936 --> 01:30:00.506
- Look, don't forget you got this on, OK?
- OK.

01:30:00.606 --> 01:30:03.008
If you need me, talk to me. It's right there.

01:30:03.108 --> 01:30:05.141
OK. Affirmative.

01:30:08.030 --> 01:30:10.070
- Sally, come here.
- What?

01:30:10.782 --> 01:30:12.782
Thank you.

01:30:18.206 --> 01:30:20.240
Over and out.

01:31:15.180 --> 01:31:17.374
Hello, Jack? Can you hear me?

01:31:17.474 --> 01:31:22.254
Like I was saying before about goin'
to New York. We could see some shows.

01:31:22.354 --> 01:31:27.301
You know, like Sugar Babies. And I know
a great hotel in the Times Square area...

01:31:27.401 --> 01:31:28.969
Sally?

01:31:29.069 --> 01:31:32.431
- Hi. I'm Frank Donahue.
- Oh, hi. Nice to meet you.

01:31:32.531 --> 01:31:35.267
Would you mind
walking with me for a moment?

01:31:35.367 --> 01:31:36.935
Where are we goin'?

01:31:37.035 --> 01:31:39.897
- I think we got a little problem.
- What's that?

01:31:39.997 --> 01:31:42.030
It sounds crazy but...

01:31:43.041 --> 01:31:46.951
I think we're being followed.
Yeah. No problem.

01:32:13.113 --> 01:32:15.724
...Gee, you're a fast walker.

01:32:15.824 --> 01:32:18.852
Well, in my business
you gotta be fast on your feet.

01:32:18.952 --> 01:32:22.481
- Where's Jack?
- Uh... Oh, he's at home, resting.

01:32:22.581 --> 01:32:25.734
- The pressure can get to you.
- Which train are we takin'?

01:32:25.834 --> 01:32:31.699
- I don't know yet. Got the tape and film?
- Yeah, right here in my bag.

01:32:45.687 --> 01:32:49.925
- I guess we lost him, huh?
- Well, we can't be too careful.

01:32:50.025 --> 01:32:55.806
Tell you what. Walk slowly down to the
end of the platform right in front of me.

01:32:55.906 --> 01:32:59.351
I don't know why you think
anyone'd wanna follow us anyway.

01:32:59.451 --> 01:33:02.771
You'd be amazed what some people
would do for a story like this.

01:33:02.871 --> 01:33:05.315
- Yeah, I guess so.
- No, don't turn around.

01:33:05.415 --> 01:33:08.318
- We don't wanna give ourselves away.
- Yeah, right.

01:33:08.418 --> 01:33:12.413
Just pretend like
nothing's happened, all right?

01:33:22.849 --> 01:33:25.878
Just look at this place.
This is disgusting.

01:33:25.978 --> 01:33:29.756
- Yeah. It's a real shame.
- And it's not even safe any more.

01:33:29.856 --> 01:33:33.385
It reminds me of that story
about that guy in New York. Remember?

01:33:33.485 --> 01:33:37.639
- Yeah, I think we did a piece on him.
- He'd ride the subways at rush hour.

01:33:37.739 --> 01:33:41.351
He'd stand in the corner real quiet
so's nobody'd notice him.

01:33:41.451 --> 01:33:46.190
Then they'd pull in to a station, he'd open
his coat and pull out a big meat cleaver,

01:33:46.290 --> 01:33:48.150
and whack 'em right over the head.

01:33:48.250 --> 01:33:52.237
- Let's go, Sally.
- And then they had this transit strike.

01:33:52.337 --> 01:33:56.116
He just disappeared.
It was like he went on strike too.

01:33:56.216 --> 01:33:57.743
So I don't ride the subways.

01:33:57.843 --> 01:34:01.330
It's not safe. I wouldn't even
come down here if it wasn't for you.

01:34:05.434 --> 01:34:07.211
Speak up. Come on.

01:34:07.311 --> 01:34:13.686
You see what I mean? See that creepy
character? It's just not safe any more.

01:34:16.445 --> 01:34:17.805
The train's coming.

01:34:17.905 --> 01:34:20.265
Franklin Bridge Express.

01:34:20.365 --> 01:34:21.934
Is that where we're goin'?

01:34:22.034 --> 01:34:25.604
- Where? Come on.
- That where they're having the fireworks?

01:34:25.704 --> 01:34:28.607
That's right.
They got a nice bar down there.

01:34:28.707 --> 01:34:33.487
Why don't we have our drink and
our little chat, then take in the fireworks?

01:34:33.587 --> 01:34:35.155
Sure, OK.

01:34:35.255 --> 01:34:38.784
- Want to help me cover the story?
- All right.

01:34:38.884 --> 01:34:41.995
- You could give us the woman's angle.
- Yeah.

01:34:42.095 --> 01:34:44.560
Franklin Bridge Express, huh?

01:34:47.309 --> 01:34:49.309
Hey.

01:34:55.025 --> 01:34:57.475
Sally. Sally.

01:34:58.153 --> 01:35:01.515
- So what's the big deal with Liberty Day?
- Did you see our story?

01:35:01.615 --> 01:35:05.015
I don't watch news. It's too depressing.

01:37:01.276 --> 01:37:03.486
Somebody get an ambulance.

01:37:04.112 --> 01:37:06.146
Try that back door.

01:37:20.796 --> 01:37:22.829
Is it 16 or 35?

01:37:22.965 --> 01:37:26.739
- What do you mean?
- The gauge of the film.

01:37:26.885 --> 01:37:30.038
They've only got 16mm equipment
out at the station.

01:37:30.138 --> 01:37:33.333
- I think that's what it is.
- Why don't you let me have a look?

01:37:33.433 --> 01:37:35.377
- Oh, sure.
- Come into the light.

01:37:47.864 --> 01:37:49.516
Here it is.

01:37:49.616 --> 01:37:51.733
- Got the tape too?
- Yeah.

01:37:53.620 --> 01:37:55.830
Yeah, that's 16 all right.

01:38:02.212 --> 01:38:04.422
Are you... wrappin' it up?

01:38:12.681 --> 01:38:15.048
What did you do that for?

01:38:15.976 --> 01:38:17.976
Jack's gonna kill you.

01:38:22.441 --> 01:38:25.110
Oh, God, no. No.

01:38:34.828 --> 01:38:37.463
One more sound and you're dead.

01:38:40.542 --> 01:38:46.079
Come on, Sally. We're gonna
cover the fireworks, remember?

01:39:53.574 --> 01:39:55.607
Jack, please.

01:40:04.626 --> 01:40:06.993
Jack. Please.

01:40:07.129 --> 01:40:09.129
No.

01:40:11.842 --> 01:40:14.459
God, Jack...

01:43:18.195 --> 01:43:20.389
...Hello, Jack? Can you hear me?

01:43:20.489 --> 01:43:25.394
Like I was saying before about goin'
to New York. We could see some shows.

01:43:25.494 --> 01:43:28.647
You know, like 'Sugar Babies'.
And I know a great hotel...

01:43:28.747 --> 01:43:33.527
...Two more young women
were killed by the Liberty Bell Strangler.

01:43:33.627 --> 01:43:37.281
But the tragedy ended when
the final victim, Sally Badina,

01:43:37.381 --> 01:43:41.618
killed her attacker in a bloody struggle
on the top of the Port of History building...

01:43:41.718 --> 01:43:44.454
...during the Liberty
Day firework celebration.

01:43:44.554 --> 01:43:48.333
The identity of the strangler
has not yet been determined.

01:43:48.433 --> 01:43:53.005
Governor McRyan's death continues to
send shock waves throughout the nation.

01:43:54.856 --> 01:43:56.550
...Oh, Jack.

01:43:56.650 --> 01:44:01.269
Oh, God. Oh, please.

01:44:08.328 --> 01:44:11.048
...Jack, please.

01:44:11.665 --> 01:44:15.116
Oh, God. God, Jack.

01:44:19.047 --> 01:44:20.574
Now, that's a scream.

01:44:20.674 --> 01:44:22.951
- How was the level?
- More on the scream.

01:44:23.051 --> 01:44:25.537
- I don't wanna distort it.
- Come on. Bring it up.

01:44:25.637 --> 01:44:30.292
- All right. I'll give it more the next time.
- That's wonderful.

01:44:30.392 --> 01:44:36.257
- What'd you think of the rest of the mix?
- Uh, OK. On the beginning...

01:44:37.566 --> 01:44:39.599
It's a good scream.

